dering tests and coverage**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the task “Add or refine tests” and how the final answer should come with some rationale. To approach this efficiently, I’ll need to inspect `COVERAGE.md`. It could provide insights into the convention for any unreachable code. I'll make sure to sift through that document carefully so that I can develop a solid understanding and ensure the tests are meaningful. Let’s make this focused and effective!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_6oTmE5z8nUeeuPJhUdqqUeOB|fc_09f4b8e6be7775bd016a1175c0cf8481a2a3e5342b9969f615", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"uncovered|unreachable|class\\$|dynamic-access\" COVERAGE.md docs tests/src -n | head -100"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 467, "output": 1494, "cacheRead": 46592, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 48553, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779529129083, "responseId": "resp_09f4b8e6be7775bd016a1175a9a69c81a29eaedb095c29c838"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_6oTmE5z8nUeeuPJhUdqqUeOB|fc_09f4b8e6be7775bd016a1175c0cf8481a2a3e5342b9969f615", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:77:  `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json` file and the dynamic-access coverage\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:90:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:93:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:319:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\ntests/src/org.springframework.cloud/spring-cloud-function-context/5.0.1/src/test/java/org_springframework_cloud/spring_cloud_function_context/PredefinedCglibProxyClassesGenerator.java:54:                BeanFactoryA